Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma says municipalities must develop protocols for communities when weather alerts are issued. Lindokuhle Xulu has more. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma says people need to know what to do when weather alerts are issued. She says local councils need to put protocols in place. READ: KZN floods | Corruption Watch calls for transparency She was visiting flood-affected areas in Durban with NGOs who have been providing relief. The Minister also says rescue teams need to be trained to deal with the effects of climate change. eNCA’s Lindokuhle Xulu shares more details in the video above.